    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on the title </span><span class=\"english\">“</span><span class=\"english\">Service Learning.”</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Use maximum ten sentences.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Service Learning</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Service learning is a dynamic approach that combines community service with academic learning. It offers students the chance to apply classroom knowledge to real-world problems, which connects theory and practice. Through servic</span><span class=\"english\">e learning, students gain a deeper understanding of the subjects they study, which makes their education more meaningful. This approach encourages critical thinking and problem-solving as students reflect on their experiences and the impact they have on th</span><span class=\"english\">e community. Service learning promotes personal growth by teaching students the value of teamwork, empathy, and social responsibility. It also allows students to develop leadership skills and gain practical experience in their field of study. Through servi</span><span class=\"english\">ce learning, students gain insight into the challenges faced by underserved communities, which fosters a sense of social justice. This form of learning encourages civic responsibility and inspires students to become active, engaged citizens. It strengthens</span><span class=\"english\"> community ties by encouraging collaboration between educational institutions and local organizations. Service learning plays a vital role in shaping responsible, aware, and engaged individuals who are committed to making positive contributions to society.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark --------------------09 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Service Learning</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">-------- </span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> ---------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Service learning is a dynamic approach that combines community service with academic learning.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">C) Context Explanation (Service Learning in Education)</span><span class=\"english\"> (Any )</span><span class=\"english\">----</span><span class=\"english\">06 Marks    </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Connects theory and practice by applying classroom knowledge to real-world problems.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Enhances understanding of subjects, making education more meaningful.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Encourages critical thinking and problem-solving through reflection on experiences and community impact.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Promotes personal growth through teaching teamwork, empathy, and social responsibility.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Develops leadership skills and practical experience in field of study.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Provides insight into challenges faced by underserved communities, fostering social justice.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Encourages civic responsibility and community ties through collaboration between educational institutions and local organizations.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">D)</span><span class=\"english\">Conclusion</span><span class=\"english\">------------</span><span class=\"english\">01Mark</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Service learning plays a vital role in shaping responsible, aware, and engaged individuals who are committed to making positive contributions to society.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Fill in each gap of the following passage with appropriate word from the given box below:</span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>5</span></p><p><span><img src=\"images/Varsity_Kha_Weekly_Live_Exam-04_Set_3_9b7f66e8.png\"/></span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A warrior of light knows that the (a)___power lies in its strong legs. The power of the (b)___lies in the (c)__with which it can spear a fish. He has learned that the reason the tiger does not (d)___the hyena is because he is aware of his (e)____strength.</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">(a) gazelle's</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(b) seagull</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(c) accuracy</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(d) fear</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(e) own</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Any mistake bears no mark. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span></p>"
