        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Irregular – The doctor warned that his </span><span class=\"english\">irregular</span><span class=\"english\"> heartbeat could cause serious health problems.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Perseverance – </span><span class=\"english\">Perseverance</span><span class=\"english\"> often separates those who achieve their goals from those who give up.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Plight – The </span><span class=\"english\">plight</span><span class=\"english\"> of refugees drew global attention and urgent calls for humanitarian aid.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Immensely – She was </span><span class=\"english\">immensely</span><span class=\"english\"> grateful to the volunteers who helped rebuild her damaged home.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Heart and soul – He put his </span><span class=\"english\">heart and soul</span><span class=\"english\"> into completing the community center on time.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">) Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. (Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii) For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii) For 02 spelling mistakes, 01 mark will be deducted, for 01 spelling mistake, 0.5 marks will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">(iv) For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a suffix or prefix, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number, etc.).</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Comment: Use the given word without changing its parts of speech.</span></p>"
